title: Ask HN: GitHub remote host id has changed
text:
Any other hackers / devs getting?

@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@ @ WARNING: REMOTE HOST IDENTIFICATION HAS CHANGED! @ @@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@ IT IS POSSIBLE THAT SOMEONE IS DOING SOMETHING NASTY! Someone could be eavesdropping on you right now (man-in-the-middle attack)! It is also possible that a host key has just been changed. The fingerprint for the RSA key sent by the remote host is SHA256:uNiVztksCsDhcc0u9e8BujQXVUpKZIDTMczCvj3tD2s. Please contact your system administrator. Add correct host key in /Users/admin/.ssh/known_hosts to get rid of this message. Offending RSA key in /Users/admin/.ssh/known_hosts:3 Host key for github.com has changed and you have requested strict checking. Host key verification failed. fatal: Could not read from remote repository.

Please make sure you have the correct access rights and the repository exists.
